[1]
Date: Wed 5 Jan 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Agence France Press, via Newsline, Tue 4 Jun 2002 [edited]

El Salvador: Dengue Fever Alert
-------------------------------
After the deaths of 3 people, Salvadoran health officials announced a
dengue fever epidemic in 3 provinces and placed the rest of the
country on alert on Tue 4 Jun 2002. "We must all work together to
eradicate the mosquito because it is the only way to combat dengue,"
said Health Minister Jose Lopez. So far this year, dengue has killed
3 children under the age of 9. The ministry said about 1031 people
have been affected since January, 83 of whom by the more dangerous
hemorrhagic variety.
The epidemic covers the central departments of La Libertad and San
Salvador, and the western department of Santa Ana. The Health
Ministry and the National Emergency Committee (COEN) have beefed up
fumigation efforts in homes, and along rivers and streams to
forestall reproduction of the _Aedes aegypti_ mosquito which carries
the disease from one human to another. [_Aedes aegypti_ breeds in
small containers, not in rivers or streams. - Mod.JW]
--
