[2]
Date: Wed 5 Jun 2002
From: Pablo Nart <p.nart@virgin.net>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, Tue 3 Jun 2002 [edited]

El Salvador: Heavy Rainfall Associated Disease Outbreaks
--------------------------------------------------------
El Salvador's Health Ministry warned of an increase in the
[incidence] of dengue fever and respiratory disease due to incessant
rainfall in the Central American country. Authorities recommended
that Salvadorans protect themselves against diseases common to the
rainy season, according to reports reaching here from San Salvador,
the capital of El Salvador.
The Health Ministry considers the 6756 influenza cases registered
this year in El Salvador as being alarming, while the number of
dengue fever cases has grown to 890, with 3 dead. Of the dengue fever
cases, 75 were of the hemorrhagic type.
The Health Ministry's epidemiology chief Ronaldo Hernandez said the
amount of rain falling in the latest days surpassed 100 millimeters,
forcing authorities to reinforce the campaign against dengue fever.
